hi,

we are starting "Adaptive Security and Economics Lab" (ASECOLAB) in =
london, to build interesting math models of network and security =
processes. there are several RA and PhD positions, and i am hoping that =
people interested in categories might be interested to apply for some of =
them. the advert is below.

all the best,
-- dusko

Researcher positions in information security at Royal Holloway

Text:=20
We have several doctoral and research associate positions within =
ASECOLAB, Adaptive Security and Economics Lab, founded at Royal =
Holloway, University of London by Prof Dusko Pavlovic. Some of the =
research directions of the Lab are indicated in the article "Gaming =
security by obscurity", NSPW 2011. Candidates with interests in the =
broad area of mathematical and economic models of security processes are =
encouraged to apply. Salaries will be competitive. The positions are for =
fixed term, under the standard academic conditions.

Royal Holloway is located in Egham, in the convenient and attractive =
area between London Heathrow and Windsor Great Park.=20

Please apply at http://rhul.engageats.co.uk/ The screening of the =
candidates will begin on August 20th, and will continue until the =
positions are filled. Please email Dusko.Pavlovic@rhul.ac.uk for =
informal discussions about the posts. For inquiries about the =
application process please contact Claire.Hudson@rhul.ac.uk.=20=


